\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\rho_{1}=s_{1}\sum_{n}\frac{1}{\sigma-\lambda_{n}}(\hat{\phi}_{n},Q_{s}\rho_{0})\phi_{n}
\]

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $(\hat{\phi}_{n},Q_{s}\rho_{0})$
\end_inset

 are the weighting coefficients 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
If 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma=i\omega$
\end_inset

, the expression tells us that the frequency response of the population
 density to a small sinusoidal input 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
If we expect eigenvalues of the form 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda_{n}(s)=-n^{2}\Gamma(s)+in\omega_{0}(s)$
\end_inset

, there will be a frequency response at multiples of 
\begin_inset Formula $\omega_{0}(s)$
\end_inset

