Substituting 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda_{n}(s)=-n^{2}\Gamma(s)+in\omega_{0}(s)$
\end_inset

, we find 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{1}{\sigma-\lambda_{n}}=\frac{1}{\sigma-n^{2}\Gamma(s)+in\omega_{0}}
\]

\end_inset

which clearly has a pole if 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma=n^{2}\Gamma(s)-in\omega_{0}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

